2026-04-16 12:37:01 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['polarity configuration of the fast-connection terminals between control module and load module'] hypothesis_explanation='The persistent symptom is that no voltage is reaching the lamps in the load module, even though 12V is present at the control module output relay, and all internal wiring, relay, and diode are confirmed operational. Continuity tests confirm the cables themselves are not faulty, but an observation reveals a polarity inversion at the fast-connection terminals (Control Output Cable (−) is connected to Load Input Cable (+)). Because the diode in the load module only allows current to flow when the correct polarity is applied, this polarity inversion blocks all current into the module, preventing the lamps from lighting. Therefore, the root cause is the incorrect polarity configuration at the connection between the control and load modules.'
